DataElement.preferredDefinition: The normal action performed by a structure or device.:An independently existing thing (living or nonliving).:A type of polymer produced by living organisms._Maintained by the National Center for Biotechnology Information (NCBI).  Provides information on the chemical activity of small molecules and encompasses three primary databases:  PCSubstance, which contains over 10 million records of substance information; PCCompound, which contains over 5 million unique component structures, and PCBioAssay, which contains over 190 million bioassays and bioactivity data.:One or more characters used to identify, name, or characterize the nature, properties, or contents of a thing._Generic value domain for a primitive java dataype that is a long integer (64-bit two's complement).
